The paper examines patterns of user behavior on Twitter during media events, which involves the intersection of social media, communication, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper analyzes the impact of media events on social processes and collective sensemaking, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
